   in the Chapada Diamantina National Park (Brazil) were monitored, one
   burned in the November 2008 fire and the other unburned since the 1999
   fire. In both sites, 25 individuals were randomly labeled and monitored.
   Nine plant samplings were conducted between 2008 and 2010, during which
