Journal = {{FLORESTA E AMBIENTE}},
Year = {{2017}},
Volume = {{24}},
Abstract = {{This study aimed to evaluate the natural post-fire regeneration in dry
   grassland. We selected three sites: I and II, with occurrence of fire
   and III with no occurrence. Each site received one transect with 20
   plots of 5 x 5m (25m(2)). Diameter at ground level (DNS), total height
   and regrowth of all individuals with height >= 0.10 m and DNS <= 5.0 cm
   were measured. Sites I and II, respectively, had 436 and 387 sampled
   individuals, and 29 and 24 species. Site III had 741 individuals and 29
   species sampled. There was a significant difference in the number of
   tiller, individuals and basal area. In sites I and II, 72\% and 88\%,
   respectively, showed signs of regrowth. The fire changed the structure
   of vegetation, and regrowth was the main strategy used by species in
